  "prompt": "Can I get any job in India after finishing my graduate studies as an international student?",
  "response": "As an international student in India, getting a job can be challenging due to various factors:\n\n1. Work Permit Requirements:\n- Foreign nationals need a valid work permit\n- Employers must sponsor your work visa\n- Requires clearance from multiple government departments\n\n2. Employment Restrictions:\n- Some sectors have restrictions for foreign nationals\n- Preference is often given to Indian citizens\n- Certain jobs may require Indian citizenship\n\n3. Potential Job Opportunities:\n- Multinational companies\n- IT and technology sectors\n- Academic and research positions\n- International organizations\n- Educational institutions\n- Consulting firms\n\n4. Recommended Strategies:\n- Network extensively during studies\n- Build professional connections\n- Learn local languages\n- Develop specialized skills\n- Consider internships\n- Explore job portals specific to international candidates\n\n5. Legal Considerations:\n- Check specific visa regulations\n- Understand work permit processes\n- Consult university career services\n- Seek advice from immigration experts\n\n6. Alternative Options:\n- Start-up ecosystem\n- Entrepreneurship\n- Remote work opportunities\n- Freelancing\n- Further studies or research\n\nEach situation is unique, so individual research and professional guidance are crucial for successful job hunting in India.",
